<br>
I bought a 9k horse for my level 9 SK twink when SoL first became live.  I loved it, at the time with fungi and horse, she was medding while fighting, could cast spells, use all her combat skills on horseback, could med on horseback with book open, and pretty much remained full mana/full health while soloing reds.<br>
<br>
Even with the horse medding nerf from VI she could still med with book open when not fighting and I liked it enough to save for the 103k one for my main a 60 rogue and thought you might like to know...<br>
<br>
1) Rogues cannot backstab on horseback; yet my SK could slam.<br>
<br>
2) We cannot hide; which means we cannot evade on horseback.  <br>
<br>
3) We cannot sneak; which means we can't invis on horseback, while my SK could use circlet and cast gather shadows and invis the horse too.<br>
<br>
So I decided ok 103k screw the possibility of a whole new level of enjoyment coming to the next PoG or 10th War.  I had previously watched 60 SK's and Paly's on their Holy and Unholy Steeds quickly reach the next wave of giants and be able to engage in full combat with envy.  No backstab and no evade, Rogues can only use it for fast travel in outdoor zones and whoops may need invis...so a friend made me a Gnomish Vanishing Device, which by the way invises you and the horse, for a little less then an invis potion.  And now finally, I have been fortunate enough to get Tiny Cloak of Darkest Night from Caller Quest in FG and I can invis my horse and I for free, of course this item only works for rogues 55 and over.<br>
<br>
Guess since I have little hope of VI making horses more rogue friendly, I can only say, let the Rogue buyer beware.<br>
<br>
Dalwhinnie<br>
